spirit:component.spirit:name: tri_mode_eth_mac_v5_4
spirit:component.spirit:description: The TEMAC LogiCORE(TM) is designed to the IEEE 802.3-2008 standard specification and supports full and half duplex operation at 10Mbps, 100Mbps and 1Gbps speeds. In addition, it provides support for VLAN and JUMBO frames, as well as network management options such as statistics gathering and flow control. The core can be configured and monitored through an AXI interface, providing users with the flexibility to select the processor best suited to their specific application. The standalone core provides either a Gigabit Media Independent Interface (GMII) or a Reduced Gigabit Media Independent Interface (RGMII), both of which can carry ethernet traffic at all three speeds and are suitable for connection to all industry standard PHYs of all media types. In addition, the core seemlessly interfaces to the Ethernet 1000BASE-X PCS/PMA or SGMII LogiCORE which can provide a Serial-GMII (SGMII) or can alternatively extend the functionality of the core to provide a 1000BASE-X PCS/PMA (1Gb/s Optical PHY Standard) creating a complete GigE MAC core solution.
